 :tx/rationale "Create task: CE-7: Session daemon — ArcSwap store server with Unix socket (ADR-STORE-018, ADR-STORE-019). BACKGROUND: With MaterializedViews, embedded mode drops to ~1s (store.bin deserialization). The daemon eliminates even that by holding ArcSwap<Arc<Store>> in memory. Also enables W_alpha and CRDT sync. APPROACH: (1) New crate/module: crates/braid/src/daemon.rs. Single-threaded tokio runtime (store is not Send). (2) ArcSwap<Arc<Store>> for snapshot isolation (ADR-STORE-018): readers call store.load() for Arc<Store>, writer applies tx then swaps. (3) Protocol: JSON-lines over Unix socket at .braid/braid.sock. Request types: {op:'transact', datoms:[...]}, {op:'query', attribute:'...'}, {op:'fitness'}, {op:'coherence'}, {op:'apply_command', cmd:'status', args:{...}}, {op:'ping'}, {op:'record_telemetry', datoms:[...]} (W_alpha). Response: {ok:true, result:{...}} or {ok:false, error:'...'}. (4) Store-server model: daemon exposes store operations, not CLI commands. CLI translates user commands into store ops. apply_command is backward-compat wrapper. (5) Socket permissions 0600. Timeout 120s per request. (6) On transact/apply_command that mutates: apply_tx to store, swap Arc, write txn to disk async. ACCEPTANCE: (A) Daemon listens on .braid/braid.sock. (B) ping responds in < 1ms. (C) fitness responds in < 1ms (reads from views). (D) transact applies and persists to disk. (E) Multiple sequential requests succeed. (F) Socket cleaned up on exit. DEPENDS-ON: CE-2 (apply_tx, t-d6e3a751). FILE: crates/braid/src/daemon.rs (new). TRACES-TO: ADR-STORE-018, ADR-STORE-019, INV-INTERFACE-008."
